gr.interamerican.bo2.impl.open.runtime
Class AbstractBo2RuntimeCmd

java.lang.Object
  gr.interamerican.bo2.impl.open.runtime.RuntimeCommand
      gr.interamerican.bo2.impl.open.runtime.AbstractBo2RuntimeCmd
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractUncheckedBo2RuntimeCmd, UnitTestCmd
public abstract class AbstractBo2RuntimeCmd
extends RuntimeCommand

AbstractBo2RuntimeCmd is an RuntimeCommand that can be implemented without defining an Operation. The class has an operation that wraps its abstract work(). method. It is possible to create Bo2 objects of any type as PersistentObject, PersistenceWorker and any other Worker type inside the work() method. The default object factories of Bo2 are used for object creation. Workers created by the open(clazz) and openPw(clazz) methods live as children of the operation.
